\noun default
\color inherit

\begin_inset Formula $\cap$
\end_inset

-stable.
 As an auxiliary device fix 
\begin_inset Formula $D\subset\delta\left(\mathcal{G}\right)$
\end_inset

 and define
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\mathcal{D}_{D}\equiv\left\{ Q\subset X\,:\, Q\cap D\in\delta\left(\mathcal{G}\right)\right\} 
\]

\end_inset


\family roman
\series medium
\shape up
\size normal
\emph off
\bar no
\strikeout off
\uuline off
\uwave off
\noun off
\color none

\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{D}_{D}$
\end_inset

 is a Dynkin system.
 Then since 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{G}\subset\delta\left(\mathcal{G}\right)$
\end_inset

 and since 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{G}$
\end_inset

 is 
\begin_inset Formula $\cap$
\end_inset

-stable 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{G}\subset\mathcal{D}_{G}$
\end_inset

 for all 
\begin_inset Formula $G\in\mathcal{G}$
\end_inset

.
 Why? Well 
\family default
\series default
\shape default
\size default
\emph default
\bar default
\strikeout default
\uuline default
\uwave default
\noun default
\color inherit

\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\mathcal{D}_{G}\equiv\left\{ Q\subset X\,:\, Q\cap G\in\delta\left(\mathcal{G}\right)\right\} 
\]

\end_inset

 and by 
\family roman
\series medium
\shape up
\size normal
\emph off
\bar no
\strikeout off
\uuline off
\uwave off
\noun off
\color none

\begin_inset Formula $\cap$
\end_inset

-stability of 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{G}$
\end_inset

 we have that for 
\begin_inset Formula $Q\in\mathcal{G}$
\end_inset

 it's the case that 
\begin_inset Formula $G\cap Q\in\mathcal{G}\subset\delta\left(\mathcal{G}\right)$
\end_inset

 and so 
\begin_inset Formula $G\cap Q\in\delta\left(\mathcal{G}\right)$
\end_inset

.
 But because 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{D}_{G}$
\end_inset

 is a Dynkin system 
\begin_inset Formula $\delta\left(\mathcal{G}\right)\subset\mathcal{D}_{G}$
\end_inset

.
 This is the important consequence of 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{G}\subset\mathcal{D}_{G}$
\end_inset

 for all 
\begin_inset Formula $G\in\mathcal{G}$
\end_inset


\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

.
 Consequently if 
\begin_inset Formula $D\in\delta\left(\mathcal{G}\right)$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $G\in\mathcal{G}$
\end_inset

 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
D\cap G\in\delta\left(\mathcal{G}\right)\,\,\forall G\in\mathcal{G},\forall D\in\delta\left(\mathcal{G}\right)
\]

\end_inset

because 
\begin_inset Formula $\delta\left(\mathcal{G}\right)\subset\mathcal{D}_{G}$
\end_inset

 and the definition of 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{D}_{G}$
\end_inset

, meaning all 
\begin_inset Formula $D\in\delta\left(\mathcal{G}\right)$
\end_inset

 are such that their intersection with the any 
\begin_inset Formula $G$
\end_inset

 in 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{D}_{G}$
\end_inset

 is in again in 
\begin_inset Formula $\delta\left(\mathcal{G}\right)$
\end_inset

.
 So then by flipping the intersection we have that 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
G\cap D\in\delta\left(\mathcal{G}\right)\,\,\forall G\in\mathcal{G},\forall D\in\delta\left(\mathcal{G}\right)
\]

\end_inset

i.e.
 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{G}\subset\mathcal{D}_{D}$
\end_inset

 for all 
\begin_inset Formula $D\in\delta\left(\mathcal{G}\right)$
\end_inset

.
 But by minimality of 
\begin_inset Formula $\delta\left(\mathcal{G}\right)$
\end_inset

 we immediately have that 
\begin_inset Formula $\delta\left(\mathcal{G}\right)\subset\mathcal{D}_{D}$
\end_inset

 for all 
\begin_inset Formula $D\in\delta\left(\mathcal{G}\right)$
\end_inset

, which just says that 
\begin_inset Formula $\delta\left(\mathcal{G}\right)$
\end_inset

 is 
\family default
\series default
\shape default
\size default
\emph default
\bar default
\strikeout default
\uuline default
\uwave default
\noun default
\color inherit

\begin_inset Formula $\cap$
\end_inset

-stable.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Theorem
\begin_inset CommandInset label
LatexCommand label
name "thm:coincidemeas"

\end_inset

If 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{G}$
\end_inset

 is 
\begin_inset Formula $\cap$
\end_inset

-stable and there exists an exhausting sequence 
\begin_inset Formula $G_{j}\uparrow\mathcal{G}$
\end_inset

 then any two measures 
\begin_inset Formula $\mu,\nu$
\end_inset

 that are equal on 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{G}$
\end_inset

 are equal on 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{A}=\sigma\left(\mathcal{G}\right)$
\end_inset

.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Proof
Let 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\mathcal{D}_{j}=\left\{ A\in\mathcal{A}\,:\,\mu\left(G_{j}\cap\mathcal{A}\right)=\nu\left(G_{j}\cap\mathcal{A}\right)\right\} 
\]

\end_inset


\family roman
\series medium
\shape up
\size normal
\emph off
\bar no
\strikeout off
\uuline off
\uwave off
\noun off
\color none

\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{D}_{j}$
\end_inset

 is a Dynkin system.
 Since 
\family default
\series default
\shape default
\size default
\emph default
\bar default
\strikeout default
\uuline default
\uwave default
\noun default
\color inherit

\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{G}$
\end_inset

 is 
\begin_inset Formula $\cap$
\end_inset

-stable 
\family roman
\series medium
\shape up
\size normal
\emph off
\bar no
\strikeout off
\uuline off
\uwave off
\noun off
\color none

\begin_inset Formula $\delta\left(\mathcal{G}\right)=\sigma\left(\mathcal{G}\right)$
\end_inset

 and therefore (with a little work) 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{A}=\mathcal{D}_{j}$
\end_inset

 and hence 
\begin_inset Formula $\mu\left(G_{j}\cap\mathcal{A}\right)=\nu\left(G_{j}\cap\mathcal{A}\right)$
\end_inset

.
 Then for all 
\begin_inset Formula $A\in\mathcal{A}$
\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\mu\left(A\right)=\lim_{j\to\infty}\mu\left(G_{j}\cap\mathcal{A}\right)=\lim_{j\to\infty}\nu\left(G_{j}\cap\mathcal{A}\right)=\nu\left(A\right)
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
